This function frees the memory associated with the <tt>dll</tt> or <tt>dylib</tt> with the given name. This should be done whenever the file in question is no longer needed in the game, normally (for example) in a Game End event.
The name of the <tt>dll</tt> or <tt>dylib</tt> that you want to free
The above example code will free the memory associated with the given dll.
